  "texts": [
    "Instead, cryptocurrencies trade purely on sentiment, and most of the price spikes are created by influencers and social media.",
    "If this trend continues, we can argue that even decentralised cryptocurrencies are just decentralised Ponzi schemes and rely on a supply of new buyers to buy new tokens at higher prices.",
    "The supply of new buyers will run out eventually.",
    "Worth emphasising here is that from the five most famous Ponzi schemes of the 2020s, are allocated to cryptocurrencies (QuadrigaCX, Terra Luna, and FTX foot_3).",
    "What is really striking in this scenario is that the poorest usually learn last about the scheme and tend to lose the most."
  ],
